SOCCER - FLU - RIDDEN RANGERS TOLD TO PLAY ON . Flu - hit Glasgow Rangers , 14 points clear of their closest rivals in the Scottish premier division , have been told they must fuflfil Saturday ' s league fixture against Hibernian . The champions failed in an appeal on Friday to the Scottish League management committee to have the match postponed because of an injury and illness - created selection crisis . Manager Walter Smith asked his staff to lodge medical certificates with the League for a postponement but their plea fell on stony ground . A League spokesman said : " Rangers have 36 full professionals and 11 apprentice professionals . . . medical certificates showed they had 11 fit full professionals and eight apprentices who are fit , so the committee was not of a mind to postpone the fixture . " 
